<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="clause" searchtype="LEGISLATION CLAUSE" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[346,005] cl 18 Application of majority verdict amendments">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18" type="ext"/>[346,005]</edpnum><title searchtype="CLAUSE-TITLE">Application of majority verdict amendments</title><desig searchtype="CLAUSE-NUM"><designum>18</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subclause" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBCLAUSE">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The amendments made to this Act by the Jury Amendment (Verdicts) Act 2006 apply to criminal proceedings only if the jury is empanelled after the commencement of those amendments.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subclause" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBCLAUSE">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Despite subclause (1), those amendments do not apply in criminal proceedings where the jury is empanelled after the commencement of those amendments (<defterm><emph typestyle="bf">current offence proceedings</emph></defterm>) if:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>in earlier criminal proceedings against the accused, in relation to an offence or conduct that occurred on the same occasion as the occasion to which the current offence proceedings relate:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2.A.I"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2.A.I" type="ext"/>(i)</lilabel>
<p><text>the jury was discharged because the jurors could not reach a verdict, or</text></p>
</li><li id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2.A.II"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2.A.II" type="ext"/>(ii)</lilabel>
<p><text>a decision in those proceedings was set aside on appeal and a retrial ordered, or</text></p>
</li><li id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2.A.III"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2.A.III" type="ext"/>(iii)</lilabel>
<p><text>the trial was aborted, and</text></p>
</li></l></li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.JURAN.SCH8.CL18.2.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>the jury was empanelled in those earlier proceedings before the commencement of those amendments.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
